Introduction of long-term advanced batteries, which could power electric vehicles with a range comparable to conventional vehicles by the year 2001, will result in oil savings of 5,000 barrels per day (bpd) in 2002, growing to 150,000 bpd in 2010 as market penetration increases to 2.7 percent.
